President Trump visited Opelika, Alabama, to meet with survivors and family members affected by a recent tornado. He thanked the first responders and law enforcement for their incredible work. The President also acknowledged the devastation caused by the tornado, with one woman losing 10 members of her family. He expressed his gratitude to the people of Alabama and assured them that FEMA is providing aid and support. President Trump also mentioned the impact on Georgia and his meeting with the Governor. He concluded by thanking everyone on behalf of the country and the United States.